    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-16T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-16T06:00:00-05:00" n="797"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.86/4–1654: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 797<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1"
                            type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d797fn1">Sent also to Amman, Baghdad, Beirut, Damascus,
                        Jidda, Tel Aviv, and Jerusalem; repeated to London and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-16T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 16, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1309. My comments on two points in Department’s telegram 1274<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d797fn2">Printed as telegram 407 to Amman, Apr. 15, <ref
                            target="#d796">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> are following: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Prospects for getting parties together through <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                                >UN</gloss> at <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> or <gloss
                                target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> level to discuss general settlement are
                            dim at this time. This leaves <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss>
                            and <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>s as only <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                                >UN</gloss> bodies where there is hope of getting parties together
                            and nibbling at problem of improved frontier control (only subject now
                            open for discussion).</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>From discussions with Egyptian authorities and some of <gloss
                                target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> chairmen following specific measures
                            should help improve border situation and machinery: <list>
                                <label>(a)</label>
                                <item>Considerable expansion <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                                    observers corps.</item>
                                <label>(b)</label>
                                <item>
                                    <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> translators to conduct
                                    interrogations.</item>
                                <label>(c)</label>
                                <item>More thorough briefing of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                                    personnel before they assume duties as observers or <gloss
                                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> chairmen.</item>
                                <label>(d)</label>
                                <item>Pressure on parties to create and observe network of local
                                    commanders and police agreements.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Even-handed treatment of incidents will do more than anything to assure Arab
                    cooperation. Key element such treatment involves differentiating between
                    individual acts and those instigated or obviously condoned by governments.
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> originated publicity would appear best
                    means maintain this distinction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
